A review of the Risk Management Plan regulation has indicated that 20 % oleum is the only chemical used in a process at the site, at any one time, in quantities above the RMP threshold applicability level.  Therefore, a worst case scenario review was performed for oleum.  This chemical is used in the white oil oleum process.  The results indicated that a potential release of oleum could not affect offsite receptors under release conditions madated by the EPA.  The area potentially impacted does not contain any "sensitive receptors".  Therefore, the facility qualifies for Program Level 1 compliance in accordance with the RMP regulation.  No offsite population or sensitive receptors are within the zone of influence as defined by the EPA.

Penreco is committed to maintaining comprehensive accident prevention and emergency response programs which meet and or exceed all federal and state requirements.  Injury and Incident Free is Penreco's safety and environmental principle.  The company's environmental, safety and health policy is as follows:

Protecting the environment and the safety and health of employees, customers, contractors, communities and the public is fundamental to the way Penreco conducts its business.  To integrate environmental, safety and health management into business activities worldwide, Penreco will:

 1.   Pursue excellence in the design, construction, operation and restoration of all properties and facilities;
 2.   Be a responsible steward of all products and services;
 3.   Train and prepare employees for emergencies and other contingencies;
 4.   Communicate openly regarding business activities;
 5.   Assign clear responsibilities to all employees and contractors;
 6.   Provide employees with resources and training to meet assigned responsibilities;
 7.   Assess the potential risks of business activities;
 8.   Comply with all applicable laws and regulations;
 9.   Participate in the development of new laws, regulations and technologies;
